      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COUNTRY FORM (8) turned in a plain run last time when fifth at this track over 484m behind Kooringa Millie (28.61) in a Grade 5. Was a winner prior to that. Tough to beat if on-song. WHISPERING SALLY (1) jumped from this box and went down narrowly when a 0.8 lengths third (20.43) in a Grade 5 at Grafton over 350m latest. Has the ability and can measure up. SPARKLIN' CHIC (2) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 4.5 lengths back in third (24.34) at this track in a Grade 5 over 411m. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to her name from nine starts. Bold showing expected. OCCITANIE (7) can feature with the right run.",
